     "{\"template\":\"intro\",\"texts\":[\"The Transport Benevolent Fund CIO (TBFCIO) is a charity which offers a wide range of benefits including health, legal advice, convalescence and cash help to its members and their dependants. The TBF is run by Trustees who understand the industry and the needs of the staff.\"],\"link\":{\"image\":{}},\"image\":{},\"wrapped\":false}",
     "{\"template\":\"htag\",\"level\":\"h3\",\"value\":\"Membership in retirement\"}",
     "If you are a member of the TBFCIO, you may choose to continue your membership in retirement. It is not possible to join once you have retired.",
     "{\"template\":\"htag\",\"level\":\"h3\",\"value\":\"Contributions\"}",
     "Contributions to the TBFCIO are Â£1 a week. However membership may be free, at the discretion of the TBFCIO Trustees. Please contact TBFCIO for more details.",
     "{\"template\":\"htag\",\"level\":\"h3\",\"value\":\"On your death\"}",
     "Your dependants will continue to be treated as dependants in accordance with the TBFCIO rules provided that:",
     "{\"template\":\"bulletlist\",\"items\":[\"You were awarded free membership\",\"You were still contributing when you died and had been a contributor for at least five years while working in the public transport industry\"]}",
     "{\"template\":\"htag\",\"level\":\"h3\",\"value\":\"Contact\"}",
     "Transport Benevolent Fund CIO\u003cbr /\u003eSuite 2.7 The Loom\u003cbr /\u003e14 Gowers Walk\u003cbr /\u003eLondon\u003cbr /\u003eE1 8PY",
     "\u003cstrong\u003eTelephone: \u003c/strong\u003e 0300 333 2000",
     "\u003cstrong\u003eEmail:\u003c/strong\u003e help@tbf.org.uk\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWebsite:\u003c/strong\u003e http://www.tbf.org.uk/",
